msgctxt "UITextData/WindowMode_Description"
msgid ""
"Controls how the game window behaves on your screen.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Windowed</>:  Runs in a movable window. Easy to alt-tab and multitask, "
"but not ideal for performance.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Fullscreen</>:  Takes over your monitor for the best performance and "
"lowest input latency.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Borderless</>:  Looks like fullscreen but behaves like a window. Great "
"for smooth tabbing with only a slight performance cost."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "UITextData/FOVConstraint_Description"
msgid ""
"Controls how the screen crops in/out <Bold>IF</> you are using a wider than "
"normal screen.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Lock to X</>:  This locks the width (X-Axis) of your screen to the "
"game camera's width, and crops in the top and bottom to match your screen. "
"This keeps all the camera trickery we have working in-game.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Lock to Y</>:  This locks the height (Y-Axis) of your screen to the "
"game camera's height, and expands the sides out to match your screen. This "
"does unfortunately break a few camera trickery scenes in-game:/ So be "
"cautious when switching to this."
msgstr ""

