msgctxt "UITextData/TextureQuality_Description"
msgid ""
"Scales all texture LODs up or down.\n"
"\n"
"Helpful if you’re getting random stutters or seeing a few extremely blurry "
"textures in otherwise sharp scenes.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Needless in-depth explanation</>:  The game uses texture streaming "
"instead of traditional static texture LODs. Textures are pulled in "
"dynamically as needed and stored in a “streaming pool” on your GPU, which "
"uses a chunk of your VRAM. This usually works great, but it has two possible "
"issues:\n"
"\n"
"-- If the streaming pool gets close to maxing out your VRAM, it can cause "
"big framerate drops as it briefly exceeds what the GPU can handle.\n"
"\n"
"-- If it goes far over that limit, the engine will randomly kick a few "
"textures out of the pool to save space. Those textures fall back to their "
"lowest-detail versions, which show up as big blurry patches in the world.\n"
"\n"
"Scaling texture LODs down makes each texture smaller in memory, which helps "
"prevent the streaming pool from overflowing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "UITextData/LumenQuality_Description"
msgid ""
"Scales the detail and quality of Lumen Global Illumination.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Medium</>:  Scales back Lumen Final Gather Quality*, Lumen Scene "
"Detail**, update speed, and a few other minor settings to squeeze out extra "
"performance.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>High</>:  Raises Lumen Final Gather Quality, Scene Detail, update "
"speed, and various other settings for noticeably better GI quality.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Unreasonable</>:  There is such a thing as diminishing returns… and "
"this is it. You don’t need to go this high.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Tailored</>:  Custom Lumen settings tuned to your specific hardware.\n"
"\n"
"*<Bold>Lumen Final Gather Quality</>:  Controls how much effort Lumen puts "
"into calculating where indirect lighting should appear. Very expensive but "
"helps reduce flickery or blotchy GI.\n"
"\n"
"**<Bold>Lumen Scene Detail</>:  Controls the resolution of Lumen’s internal "
"low-res scene snapshot used for GI. Higher detail improves accuracy but "
"costs more performance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "UITextData/ReflectionQuality_Description"
msgid ""
"Scales the detail and quality of all reflections.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Medium</>:  Scales Lumen reflections down to the minimum needed to "
"look good and slightly lowers baked reflection quality.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>High</>:  Sets Lumen reflections to mid quality, enables the Surface "
"Cache*, and raises baked reflections to full quality.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Unreasonable</>:  Full ray-traced Lumen reflections at nearly double "
"quality on top of baked reflections.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Tailored</>:  Custom reflection settings tuned to your specific "
"hardware.\n"
"\n"
"*<Bold>Surface Cache</>:  A very low-resolution render of the entire scene "
"that Lumen uses to approximate reflections without tracing every bounce. "
"Great-looking results at a fraction of the cost, just less technically "
"accurate than full ray-tracing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "UITextData/ShadowQuality_Description"
msgid ""
"Scales the resolution, accuracy, and update quality of all dynamic shadows "
"in the game.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Medium</>:  Lower-resolution shadows with reduced update quality. "
"Still looks good but prioritizes performance.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>High</>:  Higher shadow resolution, cleaner contact edges, and better "
"update stability. Recommended for most systems.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Unreasonable</>:  Pushes shadow resolution and update precision to "
"extreme levels. Very sharp, very expensive, and mostly unnecessary."
msgstr ""

