msgctxt "UITextData/HWRT_Description"
msgid ""
"This setting toggles whether your GPU uses its RT (raytracing) cores.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Important</>:  This is auto-set by our tailored settings system, and "
"99% of the time is already on the best setting.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>OFF</>:  Uses software raytracing for Lumen and Shadows.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>ON</>:  Uses hardware raytracing for Lumen and Shadows. Slightly more "
"realistic for both GI and shadowing.\n"
"\n"
"<Bold>Needless Detail</>:  We auto-set this by detecting your GPU and "
"choosing the best-performing option based on our testing. If you have an RTX "
"or RX 6-series+ card, your GPU can use Hardware RT—and higher-end cards "
"almost always perform better with it on. Mid-tier cards (~RTX 3060) can go "
"either way, so you might want to experiment a bit. :)"
msgstr ""

